parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper deployment of airbags can cause serious injuries or fatalities, and the failure of airbags to deploy can leave occupants unprotected in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
airbags deploy unnecessarily
airbags deploy with excessive force
airbags shatter the windshield
airbags scatter glass and debris throughout the vehicle interior
airbags cause respiratory problems due to powder inhalation
airbags cause hearing loss or diminished hearing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right rear ABS brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts to the right while braking
the vehicle spins out of control
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the windshield bursts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seatbelts can lead to a significant risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, compromising the safety of rear seat passengers.
symptoms: Rear seatbelts break or fail
rear seatbelt anchors loosen or detach
rear seatbelts become damaged or worn out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle sticking can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses, especially in city traffic.
symptoms: Throttle sticks in the closed position
difficulty accelerating or decelerating
unpredictable vehicle behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls severely to one side
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the power steering fluid leaks
unusual noises are heard while steering.
